With 17 years of capital markets experience, she drives research, product development, fund management, and industry advocacy. She also serves as Executive Secretary of FMAN, contributes to NGX and SEC committees, and champions financial education and mentorship.

column5: Isaac Otolo is a Partner leading PwC’s Deals–Transaction Services in East Africa and Head of Capital Raising Advisory across six regional markets. With over 20 years’ experience in corporate finance, project finance, and transaction advisory, he has led major capital raises, PPP structuring, feasibility studies, and M&A engagements across multiple sectors, advising governments, development agencies, and private investors on high-impact investment strategies.

Patrick Michael Ayota is the Managing Director of NSSF, appointed after serving as Deputy Managing Director and Chief Finance Officer. He brings extensive experience in accounting, finance management, strategy, and investment oversight across the USA and Uganda. Previously Finance Director at Barclays Bank Uganda, he has led major projects and holds an MBA from the University of South Carolina and a Finance degree from Liberty University.

Sawa Nakagawa is the Executive Director of AlphaMundi Foundation, advancing SME growth in Africa and Latin America. With experience spanning impact investing, social entrepreneurship, and finance, she has led firms like ThreeArrows Impact Partner and E2 Investments. A CFA charterholder, she holds dual master’s degrees from Columbia University and is a Scott M. Johnson Fellow.

Mariam is the Executive Director at Sync Consults Limited with over 20 years in finance and investment, having managed $300+ million in transactions. She holds a CFA designation and MBA, with previous senior roles at SIMA Funds, dfcu Bank, and Barclays Bank, and extensive board experience including Buganda Land Board and Newvision Group.

Former CFO of Kasha, he helped secure over $20 million in growth funding. Founder of Calhame Financial, he supports impact ventures across Africa. A multilingual social entrepreneur, he’s been featured in Forbes Africa and CNN.

Under his leadership, Cowrywise became Nigeria’s first SEC-licensed fund management fintech.

A CFA Charterholder and Board Governor of CFA Society Nigeria, she built the firm to over ₦70 billion in assets under management within two years, earning top industry awards for excellence, governance, and consistent investment performance.

column2: Executive Board Member & Head, Financial Services
column5: Banji Fehintola is the Executive Board Member and Head of Financial Services at Africa Finance Corporation, overseeing functions such as treasury, capital markets, syndications, financial institutions, and strategic partnerships. A CFA Charterholder and Chartered Accountant, he joined AFC in 2008 and has led billions of dollars of financing for the corporation. With over two decades in finance, he also serves on the CFA Institute Board of Governors.

column2: Head of Advocacy and Policy Research, EMEA
column5: Olivier Fines is the Head of Advocacy and Capital Markets Policy Research at CFA Institute, leading global teams in analyzing regulatory and market developments shaping the investment industry. With 20 years in investment management, including roles at Rothschild & Co, BNP Paribas and Natixis, he advances CFA Institute’s mission of investor protection, ethics, and market integrity through research and policy leadership.

column2: Presidents' Council Representative, Middle East & Africa
column5: Nerina Visser is the Presidents Council Representative for the Middle East & Africa at CFA Institute and former President of CFA Society South Africa. An investment veteran and ETP specialist, she advises on capital market development and financial education across Africa. She chairs ASISA’s ETF Committee, serves on multiple exchange advisory boards, and hosts The ETF Investor podcast.

Hodan Osman is the President of the Somali Development and Reconstruction Bank, leading inclusive finance and private sector growth in Somalia. With 20+ years in banking, public finance, and development, she has advised the Central Bank, Ministry of Finance, and international partners, restoring public finance management functions and advancing debt relief. Hodan also focuses on fintech for SMEs and global development finance initiatives.

David is an investment executive with 13 years’ experience leading equity, debt, and blended finance transactions across Africa. Proven record of originating, structuring, and managing sustainable investments in agri-food, clean energy, logistics, real estate and manufacturing.

Patricia brings experience in investments and behavioural finance (psychology) to her work with pension schemes, institutional investors, and development partners. She also offers financial wellness (money therapy) programs for families and individuals. She serves on several boards and holds Kenya’s Order of the Golden Warrior (OGW). She's a Rotary Club charter member and a Paul Harris Fellow (PHF+5).

With over 25 years in investment banking, spanning research, portfolio management, and advisory, he is a CFA Charterholder, Founding President of the Investment Professionals Association of Zimbabwe, and Interim Vice-Chair of the Capital Markets Association of Zimbabwe.

column5: Bethel Tsegaye is the Managing Director of Pharo Ventures Ethiopia, part of an Africa-focused investment platform driving growth across East Africa. With over 15 years of global experience in agribusiness, fintech, healthcare, and manufacturing, she specializes in building sustainable ventures and designing innovative financing solutions that bridge funding gaps and foster inclusive, long-term economic development.

Ken Kibos is the member-elected Trustee of the Central Bank of Kenya Pension Scheme and chairs its Board Audit and Risk Committee. With over a decade in financial sector regulation and supervision at the Central Bank of Kenya, he is a CPA and CIFA professional. He is also dedicated to mentoring youth and promoting values-based leadership in his community.

Erick Mokaya is the founder of Mwango Capital, a research and media platform offering data-driven insights on African markets and emerging investment opportunities. He also leads The Transcript, a global capital markets newsletter for investors and policymakers. With a background in finance and academia, he connects African and global markets to foster informed investment and sustainable growth.

column3: Absa Bank Kenya , AIG South Africa
column5: Kedibone Imathiu is the former Co-Founder of Kazi Capital and a seasoned finance professional with over 20 years’ experience in private equity, investment banking, and fund management. A Chartered Director (SA), she serves on several boards, including Absa Bank Kenya Plc and AIG South Africa, championing governance, strategic growth, and sustainable investment across Africa and beyond.

column2: Director, Investments at Deposit Protection Fund
column5: Alan Lwetabe, CFA, CAIA, is the Director of Investments at the Deposit Protection Fund of Uganda. He brings over a decade of experience in finance, spanning sovereign funds, pension advisory, and startup development. Alan has managed over $3 billion since 2014 and is also the Founder and CIO of CountryWealth OCIO, a boutique investment firm.

Marshall Bailey has over 30 years of global experience leading major financial boards and committees across banking, markets, and regulation. He chaired MUFG Securities in EMEA and Asia (Hong Kong), LCH Group during consolidation, and the UK Financial Services Compensation Scheme. He also served on the London Stock Exchange Group board during its $29bn Refinitiv acquisition and represented Saudi Arabia’s Public Investment Fund on National Commercial Bank’s board, chairing its Risk Committee in the bank’s $15bn merger with Samba Financial Group.

Matt is the investment director at AHL, joining in 2025 after leading the agribusiness financing team at the U.S. International Development Finance Corporation. Previously, he spent seven years at Goldman Sachs across New York, Hong Kong, and London, serving as Executive Director on the structured credit trading team. He holds an MPA from Columbia, and a BA in Economics and Asian Studies from UNC Chapel Hill.

Vice President, CFA Society Ghana
column5: Adjei is the Chief Investment Officer at Black Star Group and a board member of Black Star Advisors. He launched Ghana’s first globally managed equity fund, which has consistently outperformed the S&P 500. A CFA Charterholder and Vice President of CFA Society Ghana, his career spans Barclays Wealth, Liontrust, and American Express. He holds a Master’s in Finance and a Bachelor’s in Economics.

Reginald Tumusiime is the CEO and Founder of CapitalSavvy, an investment and advisory firm supporting SME growth in Sub-Saharan Africa. Previously with Standard Chartered Bank and Stanbic Bank, he led digital banking initiatives and SME analytics. He also a co-founded a  blockchain platform Neobank and serves as the President of the Blockchain Association of Uganda. An Aspen Africa-UK Catalyst Fellow (2025), Reginald is a Statistics graduate and CFA Program Candidate.

Gilbert is the Secretary to the Board of CFA Society East Africa and a pioneer in advancing the CFA designation in Rwanda, helping grow the community from under 10 candidates to more than 200 today. A seasoned finance leader with over 20 years’ experience in tax, financial services, and infrastructure, he serves on multiple boards and is a passionate angel investor.

column2: President, The Actuarial Society of Kenya
column5: Lorraine Mukami Njue, FIA, FeASK, is the President and Chairman of The Actuarial Society of Kenya and a leading actuary in Africa, specializing in climate risk, reinsurance, governance, and sustainable insurance. She has held senior roles at African Risk Capacity, KPMG London, and Continental Re, mobilising over $73 million for resilience initiatives. A Yale Emerging Climate Fellow, she advances actuarial excellence and climate-responsive financial systems across Africa.

column5: Justus Agoti is an experienced capital markets professional with over 20 years in market operations, research, product development, and sustainable finance. He is the Senior Manager, Market Deepening at Kenya’s Capital Markets Authority, where he leads innovation and product uptake initiatives. Justus serves on key CMA committees and holds economics degrees, CMSA certification, and advanced qualifications in sustainable finance and negotiation.

Josephine is a finance professional with over 10 years’ experience and a key contributor to NSSF Uganda, East Africa’s largest pension fund. She played a central role in developing the Smart Life Fund, enhancing member-focused savings and investment options. A CFA and FCCA, she tutors CFA candidates, advises investment clubs, serves on the NSSF Sacco committee, and holds an MBA from Heriot-Watt University.

Juliet Akello is an accomplished investment professional with 12 years of experience in Uganda’s financial services industry, specializing in investment management and financial advisory. She is the Portfolio Manager at the Central Bank of Uganda and a Board Member of CFA Society East Africa. A CFA Charterholder, she holds a Master’s in Economics from Williams College and a degree in Quantitative Economics from Makerere University.

Kenneth Owera is the Acting Chief Investment Officer at NSSF Uganda, overseeing UGX 27.7 trillion (USD 7.5 billion) across fixed income, equities, real estate, and alternatives. A seasoned investment professional, he has held roles at Stanlib, SBG Securities, and NSSF. He drives long-term strategy, champions alternative investments and pension innovation, and advocates for responsible investing, financial inclusion, and the role of institutional capital in Africa’s development.
